INSERT IGNORE INTO `challenges` (id, level, ai_evaluation_guide, domain, hardness, key_takeaway, task, title, topic_taught, constraint_as_string) VALUES
(1,1,'Does the user include the target programming language?','Software Engineering','Easy','Every prompt needs a clear action verb and the target language. Vague prompts lead to [[hallucination]] where the AI guesses incorrectly.','You need AI to write a function in a Programming language that checks whether a number is even.','Say What you Want','Hallucination Basic',NULL),
(2,2,'Does the user specify their experience level so the AI calibrates the explanation?','Software Engineering','Easy','Tell the AI your background so it can pitch the explanation at the right level. This is a form of [[context]] setting.','You are a junior developer and want to understand what a binary search tree is.','Explain a Complex Concept','Audience Targeting',NULL),
(3,3,'Does the user assign a Persona (e.g., Senior Dev) and a Target Audience?','Software Engineering','Easy','Setting [[role-prompting]] is necessary because everyone has different technical knowledge. Always define your audience.','You need to explain a ''Database'' to a non-technical Product Manager.','Explain to Stakeholders','Persona Adoption',NULL),
(4,4,'Did the user explain the concept in their own words and ask the AI to verify it, correct any mistakes, and fill gaps — rather than just asking the AI to re-explain?','Software Engineering','Easy','Re-reading notes feels like learning but often isn''t. Explaining a concept in your own words and asking AI to judge it forces real understanding and reduces [[hallucination]].','You just studied a concept — like recursion or interfaces — and you want to know if you actually understood it correctly before moving on.','Check My Understanding','Self-Verification Prompting',NULL),
(5,5,'Does the user provide the code, the error message, and the expected result?','Software Engineering','Easy','Provide details of: What error are you seeing? What did you expect? What have you tried? Without [[context]], the AI is guessing blindly and may [[hallucination]].','You have code that isn''t working as expected and need an AI to help you debug it.','Fix a Bug','Contextual Debugging','<CODE>'),
(6,6,'Does the user specify a strict constraint (e.g., ''under 20 words'' or ''exactly 1 sentence'')?','Software Engineering','Easy','Without limiting via [[constraints]], AI will generate unnecessary [[token]]s that you might not need for the job to be done.','You need a name to set as the commit message for the code changes you did.','The Nano-Summarizer','Word Budgeting','<CHANGES>'),
(7,7,'Does the prompt include the phrase "Think step-by-step"?','Software Engineering','Medium','Including the phrase "Think step-by-step" forces deliberate, ordered reasoning. This is called [[chain-of-thought]] prompting.','You need the AI to solve a logic-heavy code problem without skipping steps.','Step-by-Step Logic','Chain of Thought (CoT)','<CODE>'),
(8,8,'Did the user specify an exact number AND include an explicit stop instruction (e.g., "do not suggest more than 3", "stop after the third")?','Software Engineering','Medium','Without hard [[constraints]], the LLM will keep generating until it feels "done" — which is unpredictable. Use explicit stop [[instruction]]s.','You need the AI to generate exactly N items (e.g., N code suggestions, N test cases, N refactoring ideas) — no more, no less.','Limit to a Number','Output Control: Stop Sequences',NULL),
(9,9,'Did the user mention their current skill level, the goal they are working toward, and ask for an ordered path rather than a random list?','Software Engineering','Easy','Asking "how do I learn Java?" gets a topic dump. Asking for an ordered roadmap with a goal gets a structured path. Always provide [[context]] about your current level.','You are new to programming and want AI to give you a step-by-step learning roadmap for a specific language or skill — not just a list of topics.','The Beginner''s Roadmap','Structured Learning Path',NULL),
(10,10,'Does the user specify a structure (e.g., Usage, Parameters, Examples)?','Software Engineering','Easy','Say what [[output-format]] you want, else the LLM will guess based on its heavily trained data.','You have a messy piece of code and need a professional README section for it.','The Documentation Architect','Output Formatting','<CODE>'),
(11,11,'Does the user include the word <DOCUMENT> AND explicitly instruct the AI to use only that document, rejecting outside knowledge?','Software Engineering','Medium','Without the [[grounding]] instruction to use only the provided document, the AI blends its training data with your document silently, causing [[hallucination]].','You have a product''s documentation and want AI to answer questions or generate content strictly from it — without mixing in its own trained knowledge.','Draw the Boundaries','Grounding Knowledge Set','<DOCUMENT>'),
(12,1,'Does the user share column names and data types rather than just saying ''here is my data''?','Data Science','Easy','Share column names, types, and a sample row so the AI has full [[context]]. This is essential for accurate analysis.','You have a CSV of customer purchase history and want an AI to describe its structure and suggest analysis directions.','Describe a Dataset','Context Setting',NULL),
(13,2,'Does the user list each step they want: shape, nulls, distributions, correlations?','Data Science','Medium','Break EDA into explicit steps using [[chain-of-thought]] rather than asking for "an EDA script".','You want an AI to write a complete exploratory data analysis script for a DataFrame.','Write a Python EDA Script','Step-by-Step Instruction',NULL),
(14,3,'Does the user paste the actual numbers and ask for a specific interpretation format?','Data Science','Medium','Paste the raw metrics and tell the AI what [[output-format]] the interpretation should take.','You trained a classification model and want an AI to interpret the confusion matrix and classification report.','Interpret Model Results','Output Specification',NULL),
(15,4,'Does the user list every quality issue explicitly rather than saying ''clean my data''?','Data Science','Medium','List each problem explicitly as [[constraints]]: nulls in which columns, which columns have duplicates, what casing issues exist.','You have a DataFrame with missing values, duplicate rows, and inconsistent string casing and want cleaning code.','Clean Messy Data','Constraint Specification',NULL),
(16,5,'Does the user ask the AI to reason through trade-offs before giving a recommendation?','Data Science','Hard','Ask the AI to compare approaches against your [[constraints]] before picking one. This is [[chain-of-thought]] reasoning applied to decision-making.','You are building a recommendation system and are unsure whether to use collaborative filtering or content-based filtering.','Choose the Right Model','Chain of Thought',NULL),
(17,6,'Does the user specify the target variable, the time window, and ask for domain reasoning?','Data Science','Hard','State your target variable, available raw columns, and ask the AI to reason about which features matter. Combine [[role-prompting]] with specific [[context]].','You have raw user event logs and want to engineer features for a churn prediction model.','Write a Feature Engineering Pipeline','Role + Specificity',NULL),
(18,1,'Does the user specify length, audience, and required sections?','Business Writing','Easy','Specify the document [[output-format]]: length, sections, and who will read it. Include [[constraints]] on length.','Your manager asked you to write a one-page proposal for a new internal tool.','Write a Project Proposal','Format Specification',NULL),
(19,2,'Does the user give the key topics and ask for a specific length?','Business Writing','Easy','Give the AI the key decisions made and cap the output length with [[constraints]]. Every extra [[token]] wastes the reader''s time.','A 90-minute planning meeting just ended and you need to send a summary email to all attendees.','Draft a Meeting Summary','Conciseness Prompting',NULL),
(20,3,'Does the user specify the tone balance between positive and constructive?','Business Writing','Medium','Tell the AI the tone ratio and give specific [[examples]] to reference. Tone is a crucial [[constraints]] in professional writing.','You need to write a constructive performance review for a team member who is technically strong but misses deadlines.','Write a Performance Review','Tone Control',NULL),
(21,4,'Does the user ask the AI to write from a specific professional persona and specify the goal of the response?','Business Writing','Medium','Define the writer''s role with [[role-prompting]] and specify the outcome you want: apology, resolution, retention.','An important client emailed complaining about a delayed product delivery and you need to respond professionally.','Respond to a Client Complaint','Persona Prompting',NULL),
(22,5,'Does the user specify word count, audience background, and what the CEO cares about?','Business Writing','Hard','Always state the reader''s decision-making [[context]] — what do they need to act on? Combine with strict length [[constraints]].','You have a 20-page technical report and need a half-page executive summary for the CEO.','Write an Executive Summary','Length + Audience',NULL),
(23,1,'Does the user describe the mood, setting details, and narrative perspective?','Creative Writing','Easy','Specify POV, tense, mood, and at least two sensory details to anchor the scene. Rich [[context]] creates better atmosphere.','You want an AI to write the opening paragraph of a short story set in a futuristic Mumbai.','Write a Short Story Opening','Atmosphere Prompting',NULL),
(24,2,'Does the user define each character''s voice, motivation, and what they are not saying?','Creative Writing','Easy','Give each character a distinct speech pattern and a hidden agenda. [[role-prompting]] applies to fictional characters too.','You want an AI to write a conversation between two characters who distrust each other.','Write Dialogue','Character Voice',NULL),
(25,3,'Does the user paste the original text and name a specific style archetype or reference?','Creative Writing','Medium','Name a specific style or provide [[examples]] — "write like a YC pitch" is more useful than "make it casual".','You have a paragraph written in formal academic style and want it rewritten in the voice of a startup pitch.','Rewrite in a Different Style','Style Transfer',NULL),
(26,4,'Does the user specify the target buyer persona and ask for sensory or emotional language?','Creative Writing','Medium','Tell the AI who the buyer is via [[context]] and what feeling the product should evoke. Audience [[context]] shapes language choices.','You need compelling copy for a new wireless keyboard targeted at developers.','Write a Product Description','Sensory Language',NULL),
(27,5,'Does the user ask the AI to write from inside the villain''s worldview, not outside it?','Creative Writing','Hard','Tell the AI to write as if the villain genuinely believes they are the hero. Advanced [[role-prompting]] requires inhabiting a worldview.','You want an AI to write a villain''s speech that makes the audience partly sympathize with them.','Write a Villain''s Monologue','Perspective Shifting',NULL),
(28,1,'Does the user ask for multiple variants with different emotional angles?','Marketing','Easy','Ask for 3–5 variants targeting different psychological triggers: curiosity, urgency, benefit. Use [[few-shot]] [[examples]] of good subject lines.','You are launching a new feature and need subject lines for a promotional email campaign.','Write an Email Subject Line','A/B Variant Prompting',NULL),
(29,2,'Does the user specify the platform and its character/tone conventions?','Marketing','Easy','Each platform has different tone and [[constraints]] — always specify which one. Platform [[context]] changes everything.','You want to promote a blog post about Spring Boot on social media.','Write a Social Media Post','Platform Awareness',NULL),
(30,3,'Does the user specify the framework or structure the AI should follow?','Marketing','Medium','Ask the AI to follow AIDA: Attention → Interest → Desire → Action. Frameworks provide implicit [[constraints]] for structure.','You need Google search ad copy for a coding bootcamp targeting college students.','Write Ad Copy','AIDA Framework',NULL),
(31,4,'Does the user provide quantitative results and ask the AI to structure around them?','Marketing','Medium','Center the case study on specific numbers — vague claims kill credibility. [[grounding]] in evidence prevents [[hallucination]].','You have a client success story and need to turn raw notes into a polished case study.','Write a Case Study','Evidence-Based Prompting',NULL),
(32,5,'Does the user ask for benefit-led headlines rather than feature descriptions?','Marketing','Hard','The best headlines sell the outcome, not the tool — ask the AI to lead with the user''s gain. Clear [[instruction]]s shape the output.','You are redesigning a SaaS landing page and need a headline that converts visitors.','Write a Landing Page Headline','Benefit vs Feature',NULL),
(33,6,'Does the user specify the output format (table, list), posting frequency, and content pillars?','Marketing','Hard','Define the [[output-format]] explicitly — column names, rows, and number of entries. Structured [[output-format]] prevents rambling.','You are a solo founder and need a one-month content calendar for LinkedIn to build your personal brand.','Build a Content Calendar','Structured Output',NULL);
INSERT IGNORE INTO `glossary_terms` (id, term_key, term_display, definition, category, created_at) VALUES
(48,'hallucination','Hallucination','When an AI generates false or fabricated information that sounds plausible but is not factually accurate. Caused by vague prompts or lack of grounding.','concept','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(49,'prompt','Prompt','The input text or instruction you give to an AI model to guide its response.','concept','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(50,'token','Token','A unit of text that AI models process. Roughly 4 characters or about 3/4 of a word in English. More tokens = higher cost.','concept','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(51,'context','Context','Background information provided in the prompt that helps the AI understand the situation, requirements, and constraints better.','concept','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(52,'context-window','Context Window','The maximum amount of text (tokens) an AI model can process at once, including both input and output.','concept','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(53,'zero-shot','Zero-Shot Prompting','Asking the AI to perform a task without providing any examples. The model relies solely on its training and your instructions.','technique','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(54,'one-shot','One-Shot Prompting','Providing exactly one example in your prompt to demonstrate the desired output format or behavior.','technique','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(55,'few-shot','Few-Shot Prompting','Providing 2-5 examples in your prompt to help the AI understand the pattern or format you want.','technique','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(56,'chain-of-thought','Chain-of-Thought (CoT)','A prompting technique that encourages the AI to break down complex problems into step-by-step reasoning. Use "think step by step".','technique','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(57,'role-prompting','Role Prompting','Assigning a specific persona or role to the AI (e.g., "You are an expert Python developer") to shape its responses and expertise level.','technique','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(58,'system-prompt','System Prompt','Initial instructions that set the AI behavior, personality, and constraints for an entire conversation.','technique','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(59,'grounding','Grounding','Anchoring AI responses to specific facts, documents, or data sources to reduce hallucinations and improve accuracy.','technique','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(60,'instruction','Instruction','The specific task or action you want the AI to perform, stated clearly and directly in the prompt.','component','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(61,'constraints','Constraints','Limitations or rules specified in the prompt such as word limits, format requirements, topics to avoid, or output boundaries.','component','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(62,'examples','Examples','Sample inputs and outputs included in the prompt to demonstrate the desired pattern or format (few-shot learning).','component','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(63,'output-format','Output Format','Specifying the structure of the response (JSON, markdown, bullet points, table, etc.) for consistent and parseable results.','component','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(64,'delimiter','Delimiter','Characters or symbols (like ```, ###, ---) used to clearly separate different sections of a prompt.','component','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(65,'temperature','Temperature','A parameter (typically 0-2) controlling randomness in AI outputs. Lower values = more focused/deterministic, higher = more creative/random.','parameter','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(66,'rag','RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation)','Enhancing AI responses by first retrieving relevant documents or data, then generating answers based on that retrieved context.','technique','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(67,'prompt-injection','Prompt Injection','A security vulnerability where malicious user input attempts to override or manipulate the AI original instructions.','issue','2026-04-06 19:07:26'),
(68,'bias','Bias','Systematic errors or prejudices in AI outputs that reflect imbalances or stereotypes present in training data.','issue','2026-04-06 19:07:26');
